               <msContents>
                  <summary>letter sent to Apa Ephiphanios by someone "his servant." It mentions Pesynthe. The sender asks Epiphanios, "trouble yourself because of God and come and talk to my father."</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">15 lines of writing on the front, back blank.</note>
                     <note type="general">incomplete on the top and bottom left corners</note>
                     <note type="general">no. 9 penciled in the back</note>
                     <note type="general">written in a neat and proficient hand with literary characteristics</note>
                     <note type="general">this letter was found together with other three (23.3.702, 706, and 708 [3835]) in a tomb that was the occasional residence of Epiphanios</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="egy-Copt">in Coptic</textLang>
